definition: to mark out/to tag/to put a sign on sth explaining or calling attention to/to annotate (e.g. a character with its pinyin)

mark/sign/label/to mark with a symbol, label, lettering etc/to bear (a brand name, registration number etc)/prize/award/bid/target/quota/(old) the topmost branches of a tree/visible symptom/classifier for military units
to inject/to pour into/to concentrate/to pay attention/stake (gambling)/classifier for sums of money/variant of 註|注[zhu4]

sentences.english: Trademark registrants enjoy trademark rights and receive protection under law.
sentences.chinese: 商标注册人享有商标权，受法律保护。

sentences.english: Readings must be completed before the class number noted.
sentences.chinese: 在每堂课上课前，需读完该课标注中的阅读资料。

sentences.english: The main technical parameters of bearing and gear should be indicated in assembling drawings.
sentences.chinese: 轴承与齿轮的主要技术参数都要在装配图中标注出来。

sentences.english: I have charted this at the top of the board here.
sentences.chinese: 我在屏幕的上方有所标注。

sentences.english: These boxes can also hold the descriptions of these components.
sentences.chinese: 这些可以在框子旁边标注这些组件的描述。

sentences.english: Africa was noted to have the world's highest mountain and longest river.
sentences.chinese: 非洲被标注着拥有世界上最高的山峰和最长的河流。

sentences.english: The welding and welded joint marking method of U type pipe in furnace for platinum reforming was introduced.
sentences.chinese: 介绍了铂重整加热炉U型炉管的焊接与焊缝标注方法。

sentences.english: Can I make some notes on the question paper?
sentences.chinese: 我是否可以在答卷上做标注？

sentences.english: This paper first explores unsupervised part-of-speech tagging for Chinese via monolingual corpus.
sentences.chinese: 本文首先探索了基于单语料库的无监督中文词性标注。

sentences.english: Do you guys label genetically modified foods in South Korea?
sentences.chinese: 韩国也会标注有转基因的食品吗？

sentences.english: fastened together a Google Maps "mash-up" that plots new swine-flu cases in real time.
sentences.chinese: 则通过谷歌地图实时标注新的猪流感病例发现地。

sentences.english: We have registered the brand name, Only Education Group, as a trademark all over China.
sentences.chinese: 我司已将昂立稚慧谷于全中国进行了商标注册。

sentences.english: But the idea is that you want to make it very clear what copyrights you have.
sentences.chinese: 而中心思想就是，你需要清楚地标注出你拥有的版权。

sentences.english: ToBI (Tones and Break Indices) is currently a widely-used prosodic labeling system.
sentences.chinese: 是目前国际上较为流行的韵律标注体系。

sentences.english: They say the label is to do with the colour of a typical Korean broth.
sentences.chinese: 他们认为这样的标注和韩国传统汤羹的颜色有关。

sentences.english: We'll put some labels on these things.
sentences.chinese: 我们会把标签标注在这些东西上。

definition: variant of 標誌|标志[biao1 zhi4]
model or template character/written slogan or phrase/mention (e.g. "air mail" 航空 on a letter, "first draft" 初稿 on a document etc)
(technical) manual/(book of) directions/synopsis (of a play or film)/specification (patent)/CL:本[ben3]
